      • populateTable

        public void populateTable(java.lang.String[][] tContent,
                          Table t,
                          int[] headerRow)
        Writes the content from a String[][] into the provided table.
        Parameters:
        tContent - has the content, which has to be populated
        t - has the table, which is populated
        headerRow - holds the indexes for header rows. This rows are skipped, because they do not belong to the content. Likewise these rows do not increase the row id, thus table row id and parsed table row id maid slightly differ depending on the header.
